            <fr:title text="limitations of the pumping lemma">limitations of the <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-018N.xml" title="the pumping lemma for regular languages" addr="jms-018N" type="local">pumping lemma</fr:link></fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Warning</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter><html:p>Although the <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-018N.xml" title="the pumping lemma for regular languages" addr="jms-018N" type="local">pumping lemma</fr:link> can be used to prove that many specific <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-016M.xml" title="formal language" addr="jms-016M" type="local">languages</fr:link> are not <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-017Y.xml" title="regular language" addr="jms-017Y" type="local">regular</fr:link> there nonetheless exist non-<fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-017Y.xml" title="regular language" addr="jms-017Y" type="local">regular</fr:link> <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-016M.xml" title="formal language" addr="jms-016M" type="local">languages</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[L]]></fr:tex> for which there exists <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\ell \geq 1]]></fr:tex> satisfying the <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-018L.xml" title="the pumping property" addr="jms-018L" type="local">pumping property</fr:link> with respect to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[L]]></fr:tex>. This means that the <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-018N.xml" title="the pumping lemma for regular languages" addr="jms-018N" type="local">pumping lemma</fr:link> cannot be used to prove that such <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[L]]></fr:tex> are not <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-017Y.xml" title="regular language" addr="jms-017Y" type="local">regular</fr:link>. For example, the number <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[1]]></fr:tex> satisfies the <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-018L.xml" title="the pumping property" addr="jms-018L" type="local">pumping property</fr:link> for the following non-<fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-017Y.xml" title="regular language" addr="jms-017Y" type="local">regular</fr:link> <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-016M.xml" title="formal language" addr="jms-016M" type="local">language</fr:link>:</html:p><fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
 L =
 {\mathopen {}\left \{c^m a^n b^n\,\middle \vert \,m\geq  1 \land  n\geq  0\right \}\mathclose {}}
 \cup 
 {\mathopen {}\left \{a^m b^n\,\middle \vert \,m,n\geq  0\right \}\mathclose {}}
]]></fr:tex>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2025</fr:year><fr:month>2</fr:month><fr:day>16</fr:day></fr:date><fr:addr>jms-018S/0</fr:addr><fr:route>https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-018S/0.xml</fr:route><fr:title text="limitations of the pumping lemma › forest://jonmsterling/jms-018S/0"><fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-018S.xml" title="limitations of the pumping lemma" addr="jms-018S" type="local">limitations of the <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-018N.xml" title="the pumping lemma for regular languages" addr="jms-018N" type="local">pumping lemma</fr:link></fr:link> › jms-018S/0</fr:title><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <html:p>For non-empty <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[w=xw'\in  L]]></fr:tex> for <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x\in  {\mathopen {}\left \{a,b,c\right \}\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>, we can use the <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-018K.xml" title="pumping bracket" addr="jms-018K" type="local">pumping bracket</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (\epsilon ,x,w'\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>. Indeed, <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left \lvert \epsilon  x\right \rvert \mathclose {}}={\mathopen {}\left \lvert x\right \rvert \mathclose {}}=1\geq  1]]></fr:tex>, and so we need only check that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x^nw'\in  L]]></fr:tex> for all <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex>. We consider all the possibilities for <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[w']]></fr:tex> that follow from our assumption that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[xw'\in  L]]></fr:tex> and we see that we can repeat <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x]]></fr:tex> any number of times without departing <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[L]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
